Parliament, Wednesday, 13 June 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow meet with the Inter-Ministerial Task Team on plans to solve the impasse between Eskom and municipalities which are defaulting on their electricity debt. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Thursday, 14 June 2018
	Time: 09:30
	Venue: E249, National Assembly ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
